Even the biggest Eddie fans - and he IS a brilliant coach, proven over years - can't be blindly following his world cup schtick now? And if it really is only about 6 weeks every 4 years, that's pretty insulting to the 6N and all the autumn games. Top sides try to win them all.

I feel for the players. You wonder what is going on. I know that @SquidgeRugby has done a number of excellent videos on what the gameplan may be. But it seems we're not able to execute it and the players change so much too. Back room coaches change all the time. It's a mess.

I don't enjoy talk of coaches going but it feels like we either accept mediocrity and failure next year or we do something. If we pull some world cup miracle I'll happily eat humble pie but I can't see any way we even make the semis. There's daylight to the top 4 and rightly so.

At what point do we look at where we are and - the RFU - question progress? I know there are nuggets in there, but we have so much talent and seem unable to harness it. We don't seem to have any identity, any gameplan. And if it doesn't stop with Eddie, then who?

Can't argue with anything you've said on the pod and really the last three years @chjones9. As an England fan, we are all fed up of 'judge me on the world cup'. We look like a mess. Eddie is a class coach but it devalues the 6N and autumn games. Why can't we just win now?
